name: "Lost a Day Again" by Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
description: [Ballpoint pen on notebook page with minor digital color embellishment.] The type of thing I sometimes write in my notebook. Does it feel weird to read directly out of the notebook of a person you've never met? Kind of a strange thing to do, if you ask me... (That begs the question, "Why did you share this if you didn't want people reading it?" I don't know...) ---Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
